Ingredients

* 3 tbsp cane sugar
* 1/2 tsp baking powder
* 1 tbsp coconut oil, melted

Method
1. Put your flour in a bowl and form a well in the middle
2. Add cane sugar, melted coconut oil and baking powder
3. Whisk together adding the plantmilk little by little. Batter consistency should be very slightly thick
4. Heat a non-stick pan at medium heat, lightly oiled. Add a ladle and distribute evenly, to form a nice circle wait till itâ€™s cooked (about 1 minute) and flip back on the other side. Allow the crepe to cook another 30 seconds to 1 minute before removing the crepe and placing it on a plate. Continue this process until all of the batter has been used.
